# <type>(<scope>): <subject>   (max 72 chars, imperative mood)
#
# Body (wrap at 72): WHY this change, not WHAT — code shows the what.
#
# Footer:
#   BREAKING CHANGE: <what breaks + migration>
#   Refs: #123, ABC-456
#   Co-Authored-By: Name <email@example.com>
#
# Allowed <type>:
#   feat      new feature                          (MINOR)
#   fix       bug fix                              (PATCH)
#   docs      docs only
#   style     formatting, missing semicolons, etc.
#   refactor  code change, no behaviour change
#   perf      performance improvement
#   test      tests only
#   build     build system / deps (composer, npm)
#   ci        CI configuration
#   chore     other (no src or test changes)
#   revert    revert a previous commit
#
# Allowed <scope> (this repo):
#   cookie | order | product | user | shared        domain slices
#   cqrs | ddd | infra | logging | mcp              cross-cutting
#   tests | docs | config | tooling                 plumbing
#
# Examples:
#   feat(cookie): add stock-decrement business rule
#   fix(order): reject negative quantity in CreateOrderCommand
#   refactor(shared)!: rename EventBus to EventDispatcher
#
#     BREAKING CHANGE: callers must use EventDispatcher::dispatch().
